ips, plus a `filter tree:0` fetch for ancestry checks when the source advertises filter support.","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"7459536f-9052-4454-92c4-04c2dd820bd8","timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:08:57.619Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"5:`git-sync` mirrors refs from a source remote to a target remote without creating a local checkout. It uses an in-memory `go-git` object store and talks smart HTTP directly:\n7:- `info/refs` ref advertisement for source and target\n9:- `receive-pack` push to target with explicit ref update commands and a streamed packfile\n25:- `git-sync sync`: mirror source refs into the target\n26:- `git-sync replicate`: overwrite target refs to match source via relay, and fail rather than materialize locally\n77:`sync` picks the bootstrap relay path automatically when the target is empty. For non-empty targets, safe fast-forward updates also use a relay path that streams the source pack directly into target `receive-pack` without local materialization. Anything not relay-eligible (force, prune, deletes, tag retargets) falls back to a materialized path bounded by `--materialized-max-objects`.\n79:For branch filtering, ref mapping, tags, pruning, protocol selection, JSON output, and auth details, see [docs/usage.md](docs/usage.md).\n102:`git-sync` syncs the complete Git object history required for the selected refs. It does not create a shallow clone. Some planning paths may use filtered fetches, but the target receives the full objects needed for valid refs.\n104:### Is it just refs, or objects as well?\n106:Objects as well. Refs are what `git-sync` plans and updates, but it also transfers the commits, trees, blobs, and tags needed for those refs to exist on the target.\n114:Yes. It supports creating refs, updating refs, force updates with `--force`, and deleting managed refs with `--prune`. `replicate` can overwrite target refs, but it is relay-only and more restrictive than `sync`.\n123:Planning itself is cheap: ref-only round-trips, plus a `filter tree:0` fetch for ancestry checks when the source advertises filter support.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a9c95e4a-a91a-452a-bb6a-26c26a67355c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"d0406407-d612-489d-b375-1372d062af82","version":"2.1.136","gitBranch":"main"}
